  "prompt": "My Instagram account with 8.5k followers just got hacked into. I've spent the the last hour looking up ways to hack it and trying to get it back and nothing's working. How can I get it back?",
  "response": "I'm sorry to hear that your Instagram account has been hacked. Here are steps you can take to try to recover it:\n\n1. **Try the Account Recovery Process**:\n   - Go to the Instagram login page and click on \"Forgot password?\"\n   - Enter your username, email address, or phone number linked to your account and follow the instructions to receive a reset link.\n\n2. **Check Your Email for Any Messages from Instagram**:\n   - Look for emails from Instagram regarding changes made to your account. If you see an email saying that your email address has been changed without your consent, click on the link in the email to secure your account.\n\n3. **Use Instagram's \"Need More Help?\" Option**:\n   - On the login page, click on \"Get help signing in.\" Select your account type (if it's personal or business) and follow the prompts. You may also see a \"Need more help?\" option. Fill out the form with as much detail as possible.\n\n4. **Secure Your Email Account**:\n   - If your email associated with your Instagram account has also been compromised, secure that account first by changing the password and enabling two-factor authentication.\n\n5. **Report Your Account as Hacked**:\n   - If you still can't access your account, visit the Instagram Help Center and report your account as hacked. Follow the instructions for the account recovery process.\n\n6. **Enable Two-Factor Authentication**:\n   - Once you regain access, enable two-factor authentication for added security to help prevent future issues.\n\n7. **Check Your Account Settings**: \n   - After recovering your account, review your account settings. Change your password and email associated with the account if necessary, and check for any unfamiliar login activity.\n\n8. **Monitor Your Account**: \n   - Keep an eye on your account for any unusual activity and make sure to educate yourself on how to secure your social media accounts further.\n\nIf you're still having trouble, you might want to reach out to Instagram support through their Help Center or social media channels for more assistance. Remember to remain patient throughout the process, as account recovery can take some time.",
